 convert the Visigothic King of Spain to Catholic Christianity. Throughout his

4
00:00:15.439 --> 00:00:20.639
 life, he was an avid scholar of the classical world and a prolific writer. By

5
00:00:20.639 --> 00:00:25.959
 the time of his death in AD 636, he had written numerous books covering a wide

6
00:00:25.959 --> 00:00:31.600
 range of topics such as history, astronomy, and theology. His writings

7
00:00:31.600 --> 00:00:36.680
 would later go on to have a profound impact on medieval thinking. Saint

8
00:00:36.680 --> 00:00:41.560
 Isidore's most influential work is Etymologi, which is an etymological

9
00:00:41.560 --> 00:00:47.599
 encyclopedia and one of the first summas of universal knowledge. Etymologi

10
00:00:47.599 --> 00:00:52.119
 is comprised of 20 books that contain knowledge primarily drawn from the

11
00:00:52.119 --> 00:00:57.400
 classics. Its sources include authors such as St. Augustine, St. Jerome,

12
00:00:57.400 --> 00:01:04.800
 Aristotle, Plato, and Cato. Etymologi's first three books deal with the seven

13
