 liberal arts which are composed of the trivium and the quadrivium. The trivium

14
00:01:10.040 --> 00:01:16.400
 is made up of three disciplines, grammar, logic, and rhetoric. The quadrivium is

15
00:01:16.400 --> 00:01:23.240
 made up of four disciplines, arithmetic, geometry, astronomy, and music. The seven

16
00:01:23.240 --> 00:01:28.040
 disciplines that make up the trivium and the quadrivium were called the liberal

17
00:01:28.040 --> 00:01:32.680
 arts because they were considered essential for a free person to know in

18
00:01:32.680 --> 00:01:39.080
 order to actively participate in civic life. The fourth book is about medicine.

19
00:01:39.080 --> 00:01:45.520
 It includes information about the four humors, black bile, bile, blood, and phlegm.

20
00:01:45.520 --> 00:01:50.840
 The book briefly outlines diseases, remedies, and medical instruments. It also

21
00:01:50.840 --> 00:01:57.680
 discusses the three schools of medicine, empirical, logical, and methodical.

22
00:01:57.680 --> 00:02:04.320
 Book five is about law and chronology. On the subject of law, St. Isidore discusses

23
00:02:04.320 --> 00:02:09.600
 the differences between natural, civil, international, military, and public law.

24
00:02:09.600 --> 00:02:15.199
 Regarding chronology, St. Isidore covers periods of time such as days, weeks,

25
00:02:15.199 --> 00:02:23.360
 months, as well as solstices, equinoxes, seasons, and special years. The next

26
00:02:23.360 --> 00:02:28.760
 several books discuss theological topics such as God, angels, and saints, as well as

27
00:02:28.760 --> 00:02:33.440
 the Roman Catholic Church and non-christian sects. On the topic of God,

28
00:02:33.440 --> 00:02:38.720
 St. Isidore explains the Trinity, as well as the qualities and names of God

29
00:02:38.720 --> 00:02:43.760
 Regarding non-christian sects, St. Isidore mentions figures such as Zoroaster,

30
00:02:43.760 --> 00:02:50.280
 Plato, and Donatus. However, St. Isidore's most noteworthy contemporary, Muhammad,

31
00:02:50.280 --> 00:02:55.560
 is not mentioned at all. Perhaps this is because Muhammad and his followers did

32
